{
  "texts": [
    "Unsupervised deep learning methodsUnsupervised learning must be used as a complement to traditional learning methods to deal with massive unlabeled data.",
    "Training can be performed using generative models including autoencoders such as (stacked or denoising autoencoders) or VAE or GAN to initialize, replicate back and modify globally.• Generative Models: In statistical classification, two main methods are called the generative approach and the discriminative approach.",
    "These compute classifiers using several methods with varying levels of statistical modeling, such that new data instances may be produced by generative models.",
    "Discriminative models, on the other hand, distinguish between several types of data instances [180].",
    "In other words, generative models are those that capture the joint probability p(X, Y) or just p(X) if there are no labels, given a set of data examples X and a set of labels Y."
  ]
}